revision.text:
'''The 10 Under 10 Film Festival''' was created by independent [[Documentary film|documentary]] filmmaker and [[University of Texas at Austin]] Associate Professor, [[Ellen Spiro]]. The intention of the film festival is to encourage raw creativity among new filmmakers without relying on huge budgets.
Since 2002 the [[film festival]] has showcased short, high-quality, low-budget documentaries "founded on the notion that great ideas can happen on no budget and in little time.<ref>[http://www.austinchronicle.com/gyrobase/Issue/story?oid=oid:471805 Austin Chornicls]</ref> As a film professor, Spiro says she’s watched too many students get caught in the romance of film school debt and challenges filmmakers to make films with "little money but lots of substance and inventiveness".<ref>[http://www.austinchronicle.com/gyrobase/Issue/story?oid=oid:471805 The Austin Film Society Documentary Tour: 10 Under 10 and Its First Five Years]</ref>
The name expresses the informal desire to show ten films, each less than ten minutes long, costing less than $10 to make.
==See also== *[[Chechnya Film Festival]] *[[168 Hour Film Project]]
