The '''Grande Prairie Stompede''' is an agricultural event held typically at the end of May every year at Evergreen Park in [[Grande Prairie]], [[Alberta]]. Recent years have seen as many as 50,000 people attending during the 5 days of Stompede. Events held at Stompede include: [[Rodeo]], Pony Chuckwagon Racing, thoroughbred [[Chuckwagon racing|Chuckwagon Racing]] and usually a midway.
Originally called the Grande Prairie Chuckwagon Stompede, the event was first held in 1977.<ref>Logan Clow, [http://www.dailyheraldtribune.com/2015/05/31/thirty-eighth-grande-prairie-stompede-sees-younger-crowds-impresses-founders "Thirty-eighth Grande Prairie Stompede sees younger crowds, impresses founders"], ''[[Grande Prairie Daily Herald-Tribune]]'', May 31, 2015.</ref> By 2014, the event had welcomed its millionth visitor, and reported attendance in excess of 50,000.<ref>[http://www.q99live.com/news/?news_action=view&news_id=3802&ret=%2Findex.php "Millionth Customer Honored at GP Stompede"], [[CIKT-FM]], June 2, 2014.</ref> The chuckwagon races are the opening event of the [[World Professional Chuckwagon Association]] season.<ref>[http://www.calgarysun.com/2015/05/27/kirk-sutherland-aims-to-win-grande-prairie-stompede "Kirk Sutherland aims to win Grande Prairie Stompede"], ''[[Calgary Sun]]'', May 26, 2015.</ref><ref>[http://www.calgaryherald.com/sports/Rick+Fraser+wins+WPCA+season+opening+Grande+Prairie+Stompede+title/8468636/story.html "Rick Fraser wins WPCA season-opening Grande Prairie Stompede title"], ''[[Calgary Herald]]'', June 1, 2013.</ref>
